<br>
1. Balance or unbalanced<br>
2. Class perspective<br>
<br>
(1) Is it balanced for any class that is of equivalent levels, AA, and gear to:<br>
<br>
           (A) Produce on average 500 DPS (equivalent to 3 VT capable rogues.<br>
           (B) Solo content that takes 6+ people<br>
<br>
Forget the risks for a second should that be even possible to do?  (if not then the recourse is easy).  If the answer is yes it should be possible, then are the Risk Vs Reward in place for that ability?  Harder to measure the second but several enchanters on my server won't group in BoT and simply solo the minis, and some will snake a mini from you if you don't kill it fast enough for their liking.  Every charmer I have met have told me that dying a few times a night is worth the 5 AAs, parchments, and loot they get when they do it.  If that is the case then it would appear that risk vs reward is not balanced.<br>
<br>
(2) Damage is either direct or indirect.  Enchanters are described as a utility class that &quot;indirectly&quot; raises the power and capabilities of others.  <br>
<br>
In short, enchaters allow an efficiency not capable without them and allow groups to go to some areas that would otherwise be nearly impossible.  So lets looks at enchanter's indirect dps.<br>
<br>
              (A) Haste: SoV with all its bells and whistles adds probably 50% more dps to melee.  With three melee (warrior/monk/rogue) in a group with an average &quot;pre-haste&quot; dps of 60, the enchanter's &quot;indirect&quot; DPS is 90.  <br>
               (B) KEI:  I don't know by what amount in DPS it increases classes like mages and wizards but lets say 20%.  Let's say pre-kei dps for mages and wizards are 70.  Thats an additional 24 dps if two are in a group.<br>
<br>
Total Indirect DPS: 114<br>
<br>
Now throw in the real utility of 70% slow and mezzing.  Add that KEI for the cleric is allowing the group to be further optimized.  <br>
<br>
If the enchanter nukes then their number goes up.  If they cast SoV on cleric and substantially increases proc rate and damage then it goes up further.<br>
<br>
Point is, they have substantial indirect dps, which is what defines their class.  They have charm to be situational direct dps when it is needed or is needed for CC.<br>
<br>
When the charm tool is SO good that it is no longer situational but the norm AND they get all the other abilities heaped on top. Then it is truly unbalanced.<br>
<br>
When enchanters who are now in the elemental planes are saying that soloing in PoF for AA will take 15-20 as the norm then something is out of whack (taken from castersrealm enchanter forum). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andurravenblade>Andur Ravenblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#333333>(1/8/03 7:58:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAGE Elemental Silence OVERpowered! Devs Read.</span><hr size=1> Forgot to add DC'd pets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#333333>(1/8/03 8:10:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAGE Elemental Silence OVERpowered! Devs Read.</span><hr size=1> Wow Noonie, it's much easier to just claim the Enchanters are evil people out to fool you into believing their godlike powers are ok than it would be to actually LISTEN to their words or offer some form of viable alternative.<br>
